ges and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":33,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":42,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":77,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord of Streatlam Robert Trayne was born in 1182, in England, his father, Hugo Trayne, was 20 and his mother, Alice, was 20. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1182–":"1182–Surnud","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","1207–1296":"1207–1296","1162–Male":"1162–Surnud","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","1207":"1207","England":"England"},"fi":{"1182–":"1182–Kuollut","1182–Male":"1182–Kuollut","1207–1296":"1207–1296","1162–Male":"1162–Kuollut","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","1207":"1207","England":"England"},"fr":{"1182–":"1182–Décédé","1182–Male":"118